## First-time Setup

The upstream platform is cloned automatically by `start.sh` on first run. The `stellars-jupyterhub-ds/` directory is **not** a git submodule of this overlay - it's a plain clone listed in `.gitignore`, treated as read-only.

Generate a self-signed cert for your hostname:

```bash
cd certs
./certs_generate.sh \
  --cn "{{ cert_common_name }}" \
  --dns-altnames "{{ cert_dns_altnames }}"
```

Optionally install the cert to your local trust store:

```bash
./install_cert.sh {{ project_slug }}-certificate
```

## Deployment

```bash
./start.sh           # Start the stack
./start.sh --refresh # Update upstream stellars-jupyterhub-ds
./start.sh --no-pull # Skip docker pull (use locally-built images)
./stop.sh            # Stop all services
./cleanup.sh         # Reclaim Docker disk space
./cleanup.sh --all   # Also remove stopped containers and unused volumes
```

## First Admin Bootstrap

The first admin user is created in one of two modes. Both honour `JUPYTERHUB_ADMIN={{ admin_username }}` and never auto-create the admin with an unrecoverable random password.

**Self-signup (default)** - leave `JUPYTERHUB_ADMIN_PASSWORD` unset. On a fresh deployment with empty database, the signup form is silently re-opened scoped to `{{ admin_username }}` only. Visit `https://{{ jupyterhub_subdomain_prefix }}{{ base_hostname }}/hub/signup`, register as `{{ admin_username }}` with a password you choose, and log in. NativeAuthenticator self-approves that signup and the admin role is granted at login. Any other username on the signup form is rejected. Once the admin exists in the database, the bootstrap window closes.

**Provisioned** - set `JUPYTERHUB_ADMIN_PASSWORD` in `compose_override.yml`:

```yaml
- JUPYTERHUB_ADMIN_PASSWORD=<your-initial-password>
```

The hub seeds the admin record with that password on startup. The value is **initial only** - once the admin changes their password through the UI, the env value is permanently ignored.

## Branding

The `branding/` directory is mounted read-only at `/srv/branding` in the JupyterHub container. The compose override sets:

- `JUPYTERHUB_LOGO_URI=file:///srv/branding/{{ branding_prefix }}_logo.png` - login page lockup
- `JUPYTERHUB_FAVICON_URI=file:///srv/branding/favicon.ico` - browser tab
- `JUPYTERHUB_LAB_MAIN_ICON_URI=file:///srv/branding/{{ branding_prefix }}_main_icon.svg` - JupyterLab top bar
- `JUPYTERLAB_SYSTEM_NAME={{ project_name }}` - displayed system name

To rebrand: drop replacement files at the same paths.

